W. 125th Street, (left of No. 1 and 2) eastward across Morningside Avenue from an open area called Roosevelt Square. To the right is Hancock Place, extending southward to Hancock Square where it runs into St. Nicholas Avenue. The "O'Reilly" warehouse seen at the extreme right is at the N.E. corner of St. Nicholas Avenue and W. 123rd Street. The Ninth Avenue "El" is shown crossing 125th Street at Eighth Avenue. View 2 is in a northeastward direction and shows mainly the buildings on the north side of 125th Street between Morningside and St. Nicholas Avenue.

Morningside Avenue, west side, north from W. 125th Street, and showing at the N.W.corner of this point, St. Josephs Roman Catholic Church. To the rear of same is the Convent occupying a site at the S.W. corner of W.126th Street (formerly Lawrence) Street. This church was erected here in 1860 as the German Church of Manhattanville.

Views 1 and 2 are similar, while No. 3 shows the church front and the adjoining parish house. Buildings shown to the left of the latter bear No.'s 409 to 413 W. 125th Street.

The open area in the foreground is Roosevelt Square and is formed by the crossing of several thoroughfares at this point.

April 1, 1938
